.TH  rc "" "" "System Administration"
.PC "Perform standard maintenance chores"
\fB/etc/rc\fR
.PP
.II "boottime, standard chores"
The shell script
.B /etc/rc
is executed by the
.B init
process when the \*(CO system enters multi-user mode.
The commands in
.B rc
do such things as set the local time zone
and initialize file
.BR /usr/adm/wtmp ,
which holds records of user logins.
.SH "See Also"
.Xr "Administering COHERENT," administe
.Xr "brc," brc
.Xr "init" init
